# MC Plan Hygiene On Every PR

Whenever you commit work that will become (or update) a pull request, treat
Mission Control as part of the delivery — not an afterthought.

## Required before commit / PR open

1. **Project + bucket** — Confirm the work sits in the correct MC project and
   bucket (e.g. `BKT-MISSION-CONTROL-OPS`). Create or re-home the task if wrong.
2. **Task** — Checkout or create an MC task; stamp the PR body with
   `MC-Checkout: dsp_*` (one line per task).
3. **Update** — Progress notes, evidence, accountable owner, and stage must
   match reality before you claim the PR is ready.
4. **Follow-ups** — Before marking the primary task done / opening the PR,
   file explicit MC tasks for deferred work (fleet rollout, secret retirement,
   Phase 2, docs debt). Do not leave follow-ups only in chat or PR prose.

## Required at PR merge / cutover complete

- Complete the checked-out task with evidence (summary, PR URL, verification).
- Ensure every follow-up named in the PR / evidence bundle exists as an MC
  task in the right bucket with owner + done-when criteria.

## Anti-patterns

```text
❌ Ship PR #112, mention “fleet Phase 2 / retire bearer later” only in the PR body
✅ Create TASK-300 (fleet) + TASK-299 (bearer retirement) in BKT-MISSION-CONTROL-OPS

❌ Commit without checking bucket / accountable owner
✅ Search MC first; fix owner/bucket; then commit
```

## How

Prefer PLX-MC MCP / `scripts/compliance-checkout.mjs` (`mc_create_task`,
`mc_checkout_task`, `mc_complete_task`). Bucket must be a real MC bucket id.
Omit `repos` on create if the registry rejects unregistered names — put repo
scope in the description instead.
